THE Ondo State Police command have arrested a suspected arsonist, Deji Adenuga, who allegedly set ablaze eight members of his estranged girlfriend’s family. Police spokesperson Femi Joseph confirmed Adenuga’s arrest to reporters in Akure, the Ondo State capital. He said the suspect would be paraded today. Adenuga was arrested in Ijebu Ode under the Brid, Ogun State, according to the police spokesman. It was learnt that Adenuga was one of the inmates that escaped at Olokuta Prison during the 2013 jail break. He was sentenced to death in 2012 after killing his wife.